    "text": "MAIN\nSCORES\nCOLUMNS\nTEAMS\nBOARD\nSUPPORT\nINSIDE D2FOOTBALL\n\n\nGLIAC Semi Final Preview\nPrev\nNext\n1\n2\n3\nRMAC - Semifinal Preview\nDecember 6th, 2022 6:00pm\nFor the second year in a row and only the third time ever, an RMAC team is in the semifinals.  Colorado School of Mines has earned the right to be mentioned among the top teams in the country and will have the opportunity to do something the program has never done, and only one other RMAC team has done –\nRead More\nLSC Postseason Week 3 Recap\nDecember 4th, 2022 2:00pm\nSuper Region 4 Final and Bowl RecapI can’t think of a worst way this week could have gone for LSC fans.  Three games, all losses. \nRead More\nSupport D2Football\nDecember 4th, 2022 1:00pm\nSupport D2Football.comSupport Monthly via PayPal OptionsTier 1 : $10.00 USD - monthlyTier 2 :\nRead More\n2022 Playoff Bracket\nDecember 3rd, 2022 8:00pm\nRead More\nMatocha's Six-TD Day Leads Mines Back To NCAA Semis\nDecember 3rd, 2022 3:55pm\nSAN ANGELO, Texas - John Matocha guided #10/7 Colorado School of Mines back to the NCAA semifinals, willing the Orediggers past #2/2 Angelo State 42-24 to avenge a regular-season loss to the Rams in the Super Region IV final. Matocha accounted for all six of Mines'\nRead More\nFerris State Stuns GVSU, Advances to National Semifinals\nDecember 3rd, 2022 3:50pm\nThe Ferris State University Bulldogs advanced to the NCAA Division II National Semifinals for the fourth consecutive year and fifth time in the last six seasons, stunning archival Grand Valley State in a 24-21 come from behind victory on Saturday (Dec. 3) at Lubbers Stadium in Allendale.\nRead More\nArgos Roll Past Wingate Into National Semifinals\nDecember 3rd, 2022 3:48pm\nIn another mind-boggling way, UWF's football team produced its latest gem and newest rarefied place.  \nRead More\nShepherd rolls into semifinals\nDecember 3rd, 2022 3:45pm\nRecord-setting quarterback Tyson Bagent and the Shepherd University football team are heading back to the NCAA Division II semifinals. Bagent completed 19 of 28 passes for 231 yards and four touchdowns, Ronnie Brown rushed for 141 yards on 27 carries and finished with three scores, and the Rams (13-1) blew out host Indiana 48-13 on Saturday in the national quarterfinals.\nRead More\nOwens Announces Retirement at Ashland\nDecember 2nd, 2022 12:00pm\nAshland's football program hasn't seen a lot of turnover at the top in the last six-plus decades.  \nRead More\n\nTweets by D2Football\n\n\n\nCopyright © 2000-2022 D2Football.com. All rights reserved.",
